==English==
===Etymology===
Originated 1425–75 from late [[Middle English]] ''[[ostentacioun]]'', from [[Middle French]] ''ostentation'', from [[Latin]] ''ostentātiōn'' (singular of ''[[ostentatio|ostentātiō]]''), equivalent to ''[[ostentatus|ostentātus]]'' (past participle of ''[[ostentare|ostentāre]]'', to display or exhibit), [[frequentative]] of ''[[ostendere]]'' (to present, display) + ''[[-ion|-iōn]]''.

===Pronunciation===
Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪʃǝn|-eɪʃǝn]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}
# of excessive [[show]] in an attempt to impress others; [[flamboyant]], [[pretentious]].
# {{archaic}} to show or [[display]].

